This paper is primarily focused on optimization algorithms for neural network training, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of batch size on training, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research. Additionally, the use of a simple quadratic model to analyze optimization algorithms could be relevant to researchers in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and theoretical computer science (cs.THEORY). Finally, the paper's focus on generating testable predictions about neural network optimization could be of interest to researchers in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
